eply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The simple answer to whether it was an exploit</span><hr size=1> It was an exploit, there is no way you can sugarcoat it.  Am I mad that I &quot;missed out&quot; on it? No.  Am I mad that the jokers that did it will get away with it? Yes.<br>
<br>
I pay to play also.  I pay to play a game where it would nice if  people cannot cheat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwemic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wemic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 9:06:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22296.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The simple answer to whether it was an exploit</span><hr size=1> No rollbacks and probably no research on the logs to find out who got &gt; standard amount of xp given X amount of time.<br>
<br>
In the pages of history, this will be viewed as a &quot;learning experience&quot;.<br>
<br>
Kendrick said it best in another thread. I might have gone out and seen how much damage I could have done to a rat, /reported and moved on to more normal stuff.<br>
<br>
Does loosing out on a sweet deal BFG9000-ish weapon for a few hours make me feel bad? Nope. I like to think of myself as an ethical person who is also human.<br>
<br>
The human part is that there are days when I am grinding that I say, &quot;Damn I wish I could do X or Y that I clearly am not allowed to do just for a change.&quot;<br>
<br>
I cheat to high heck and back on stand-alone PC games. Adventure games and RPG's are the types I love and dang if I am going to not try out someone's utility to make a party I find interesting to play in Baldur's Gate II or the like. My money, my game, only affecting me on *single-player*.<br>
<br>
Sure, I might not play through exactly how the developer wanted, but I have fun and still get to enjoy the story of the game. Flat out, I suck badly at most games. Rather than toss something into a pile because I cannot get through a point, I'll tweek and continue on.<br>
<br>
However, I do not take this mode of thinking to multi-player. TFC = me getting creamed right off the bad and cackling all the way as I try to survive. No harm done, someone had fun turning me into gibblets and I got to play a few minutes.<br>
<br>
Same with Everquest. I want to be as big and bad-ass as some people you read about all the time. Attitudes of people aside, it would be pretty nice to have my name up as someone who helped a group kill the AoW or something. Going to happen? Who knows. Am I going to cheat to get to level 60 (+ alt), find a way to create items and s**t? No way.<br>
<br>
I've seen Bob the Newbie rocket past me in the past and no doubt Bob2 will be doing the same soon. It's a matter of playstyle. They are not bugging me, I don't bug them or really care. Makes my DING rewarding since it is my own (or group's) DING.<br>
<br>
It would piss me off though if Bob3 rocketed past and was found to be a habitual cheater.<br>
<br>
Who knows what Verant has out there to catch someone trying to cheat. Hell, for awhile there were some people cringing at the though of using a game pad to macro up fishing.<br>
<br>
Hmm... this post has gone on too long. Draw from it what you will.<br>
